    "By replacing full-scale quantum calculations with Transformer-accelerated predictions, it is promising to achieve orders-of-magnitude improvements in computational speed while maintaining precision.",
    "This enables the rapid screening of novel solid electrolytes with optimized ionic conductivity and stability, ultimately accelerating advancements in next-generation battery technologies.",
    "It is significant to build structured and multidimensional databases for screening battery materials and combine simulation results, automation tools and ML tools to realize the data collection, analytics, and modeling for object-oriented tasks.",
    "As shown in Fig. 8b, it is desirable to develop an automation dashboard embedded with ML models to rationalize new battery materials with desired properties, generating the optimized application scenarios for a battery system under extreme conditions, such as high temperature, high pressure, high charge/discharge rate, and mechanical stress.",
    "For example, we can automate the discovery of structure-property-performance relationships for batteries at extremely low temperatures by integrating variables across different scales, from atomic-level simulations to device-level performance of electrolytes."
